sion at redshifts of $\\sim0.4$, $0.8$, and~$1.5$ with LISA, LIGO-Virgo,\nand CE/ET, respectively. These far-side binaries would be the most massive BBHs\nLIGO-Virgo could detect.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 29 May 2020 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 24 Feb 2021 02:05:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-16"}
